<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>FAQ</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --scaling-factor: 0.5;
      --deck-width: 250px;
      --deck-height: 200px;
    }

    body,
    html {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      color: #000;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    .faq-section {
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 50px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #fff;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .faq-item {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .faq-question {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 12px;
      font-size: 16px;
      text-align: left;
      background-color: #ccc;
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background-color 0.3s;
    }

    .faq-question:hover {
      background-color: #999;
    }

    .faq-answer {
      display: none;
      padding: 12px;
      background-color: #eee;
      border-radius: 4px;
      margin-top: 6px;
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
      const questions = document.querySelectorAll(".faq-question");
      questions.forEach(button => {
        button.addEventListener("click", () => {
          const answer = button.nextElementSibling;
          answer.style.display = answer.style.display === "block" ? "none" : "block";
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</head>

<body>
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">How many people can play in a game?</button>
      <div class="faq-answer">4 players total per game!</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">What do the wild cards do?</button>
      <div class="faq-answer">The regular wild card allows you to choose a color, while the +4 allows the change of color along with the next player in turn drawing 4 cards.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">What if I dont call out UNO?</button>
      <div class="faq-answer">If someone calls you out on it, draw 4 cards, but if no one notices, then you're good...</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Can you reverse a +2?</button>
      <div class="faq-answer">In the official rules, no.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Can cards stack? For example, +2 then +2? Etc. </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">No cards can stack. Not even +4s.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Where can I find the official rules? </button>
      <div class="faq-answer"><a href="https://www.unorules.org/faq/" target="_blank">https://www.unorules.org/faq/</a></div>
    </div>

  </section>
</body>

</html>
